# `.somi/` — SoMi AI workflow artifacts

This directory holds the durable artifacts produced by SoMi AI's planning, coding, and review
workflows. Everything in here is committed to your repository so it travels with the work and is
visible to teammates and reviewers.

## What you'll find

**Plans** and **reviews** live in separate top-level subdirectories — all plan artifacts under
`plans/`, all review files under `reviews/`:

```
.somi/
├── README.md                       ← this file
├── plans/
│   ├── rate-limiting-webhooks/     ← one work item (slug from the problem statement)
│   │   ├── context.md              ← background, surrounding code, constraints
│   │   ├── spec.md                 ← purpose, requirements, core decisions, user story, DoD
│   │   ├── decisions.md            ← ADR-style log of architectural choices
│   │   ├── progress.md             ← single source of truth for status
│   │   ├── diary.md                ← chronological narrative: changes, blockers, discoveries
│   │   └── phases/                 ← one file per phase, iterations inside
│   │       ├── 01-define-limiter.md
│   │       ├── 02-wire-into-handler.md
│   │       └── 03-rollout.md
│   └── audit-log-rotation/         ← another work item
└── reviews/
    ├── rate-limiting-webhooks/      ← reviews scoped to this work item
    │   ├── 2026-05-21-iteration-1-1-approve.md
    │   └── 2026-05-22-iteration-1-2-request-changes.md
    └── _ad-hoc/                     ← ad-hoc reviews not scoped to a work item
        └── 2026-05-23-auth-audit.md
```

## Lifecycle

- **Work items are never auto-deleted.** They remain in `.somi/` indefinitely. Only you decide
  what to remove.
- **Status lives in `progress.md`**, not in directory location. A completed work item stays
  where it is; you'll see `status: done` in its `progress.md`.
- **Plans are not frozen.** If implementation reveals the plan needs to change, the spec/phase
  files are updated **in place** to reflect the new truth — and an entry is appended to
  `diary.md` recording what changed and why.

## How to use this directory

- **Reading existing work**: start with `plans/<slug>/progress.md` to see status, then `spec.md`
  for the what/why, then `phases/` and `decisions.md` for the how.
- **Resuming work**: invoke `/code <slug>` and SoMi AI will pick up from the current state in
  `plans/<slug>/progress.md`.
- **Reviews**: `/review` writes its output under `reviews/<slug>/` (separate from the plan
  artifacts — no clutter inside `plans/<slug>/`).
- **Archiving**: rename the work-item directory or move it under `plans/archived/<slug>/` if you
  prefer — SoMi AI tolerates this but does not require it.

## When you should edit these files directly

Any time. These are **your** artifacts. SoMi AI writes them; you own them. Common edits:

- Sharpening the user story or requirements in `spec.md`.
- Adding a phase or splitting an iteration in `phases/`.
- Marking a decision as `superseded` in `decisions.md`.
- Adding a diary entry to capture a conversation that happened outside `/code`.

If your edits change the plan (not just typo fixes), append a diary entry so future readers know
the change happened and why.
